					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A commentary on the Zohar, Raʿaya mehemana.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Aramaic of the Zohar</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="212v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Or yaḳar (Raʿaya mehemana)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אור יקר (רעיא מהימנא)</title>
							<note>
								<p>The volume contains gate 1 (folio 2r), 2 (folio 58r) and 3 (folio 135v). It begins with folio 114r of the Zohar (volume 2, in Mishpaṭim).</p>
								<p>The text of the Zohar is given on the inner part of a page where it occurs, and the commentary is written in continuous order on the top, bottom, and outer side of the page.</p>
								<p>Thre are marginal notes in an Italian cursive hand of apparently the 17th century on folios 2v-5r.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">Cordovero, Moses ben Jacob, 1522-1570</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">קורדוברו, משה, 1522-1570</persName>
							</author>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">שלם ע"י הצעיר תולעת <name type="person" role="scribe">יעקב בכמ' מרדכי פוייטי</name> יצ"ו פה <name type="place">אסטי</name> שנת ש'מ'ח'ה' [=שמ"ח] לאיש ט'ו'ב' כסלו.<locus n="212v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
