						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive and cursive scripts of the second half of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ya῾aḳov Pogeṭṭi</name>: inscribed with his initials, folio 2r, and with his name, folio 212v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1r-1v contain a list of commandments treated in the volume.</p>
							<p>Folio 2r: a scribal entry within an oblong design.</p>
						</additions>
